name: Fraxia_HDX_327390
description:
Fraxia_HDX takes a random seed and renders a very high resolution 2D map of a time-based function at a slightly-different scale to Fraxia_HD, using controlled noise within a slightly-biased HSB color model. Seed values are observed, but mostly discarded; there seems to be a small zone of viable results; when found, 30 frames rendered at 2048 x 2048. Piece name is the random seed. Although Fraxia_HD shares code with Fraxia, seed values produce differing results.
Seed parameters:
Color change choice is 3; speed is 4.751483
Parameter choice is 8; render choice is 0.
Stripe choice is 0 at 133.0, 269.0
Stripe alternate is 0 at 89.0, 212.0
